        "class": "ital",
        "text": "she shall be called",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.] The marg. by pointing out that the Hebrew for “woman” is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Isshah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and for “man” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ish",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", shews the resemblance in the sound of the two words. This is fairly reproduced in the English words “Woman” and “Man”; and in Luther’s rendering “Männin” and “Mann.” The LXX is unable to reproduce it. The Latin attempts it with questionable success, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "haec vocabitur virago, quoniam de viro sumpta est",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Instead of “from man.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mê-ish",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". LXX and Targ. read “from her husband” = ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mê-ishâh",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which adds to the resemblance in sound.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
